injury.description: Dec 1: Tonga (chest) is inactive for Monday night's contest against the Giants.
Jun 6: Hodges (knee) cleared waivers and reverted to Jacksonville's PUP list Thursday, Demetrius Harvey of The Florida Times-Union reports.
Nov 21: The Cardinals placed Williams (shoulder) on injured reserve Friday.
Oct 22: Detroit placed Cunningham (hamstring) on its injured reserve list Wednesday, Jacob Richman of mlive.com reports.
Aug 26: Bartholomew (back) was placed on the reserve/PUP list Tuesday.
Nov 29: The Panthers placed Zavala (calf) on injured reserve Saturday, Darin Gantt of the team's official site reports.
Nov 22: The Bears placed Johnson (thumb) on injured reserve Saturday.
Oct 8: Houston executive vice president and general manager Nick Caserio said Tuesday that he expects Watson (calf/Achilles) to return later this season, Sam Warren of the Houston Chronicle reports.
Nov 2: Oliver (biceps) has a chance to return for the first week of the playoffs, Ian Rapoport of NFL Network reports.
Dec 3: Lassiter (foot) did not practice Wednesday.
Dec 1: Juszczyk is dealing with a rib fracture ahead of the 49ers' bye week, David Lombardi of SFStandard.com reports.
Jul 21: Butler (knee) was placed on the active/PUP list Monday, Calvin Watkins of the Dallas Morning News reports.
Dec 3: Sewell (shoulder) is questionable for Detroit's matchup versus the Cowboys on Thursday.
Aug 26: The Ravens placed Wade (ribs) on injured reserve Tuesday, Jamison Hensley of ESPN.com reports.
Nov 26: The Seahawks designated Mills (knee) to return from the reserve/non-football injury list Wednesday, Brady Henderson of ESPN reports.
Nov 21: Taylor-Britt was placed on the injured-reserve list Friday.
Oct 14: The Titans placed Oladejo on injured reserve with a fractured leg Tuesday.
Aug 15: Oladokun (undisclosed) reverted to the Chargers' injured reserve list Friday, per the NFL's transaction log.
Nov 17: Coach Kyle Shanahan said Monday that Cowing's (hamstring) 21-day practice window will likely be opened following the 49ers' Week 14 bye, Matt Maiocco of NBC Sports Bay Area reports.
Dec 2: Tracy said Tuesday that he suffered a hip contusion/stinger during Monday's loss at New England, but he expects to be "fine," Dan Duggan of The Athletic reports.
Dec 3: Greenard (shoulder) was a limited participant at Wednesday's practice.
